Corveon integrates with, and relies on, third-party public medical data sources and
open-source software, each under its own license and terms of use — including openFDA,
DailyMed, RxNorm/RxNav (NLM), PubMed/PMC E-utilities (NCBI), ClinicalTrials.gov, MeSH,
DDInter 2.0, the AGS Beers Criteria, and STOPP/START. Users are responsible for complying
with each source's license and rate limits.

Corveon is not a medical device and does not provide medical advice. It is a human-in-the-loop
assistant for licensed professionals and never replaces clinical judgment.
